{{#IF_HAS_TYPESCRIPT}}
## TypeScript Rules

- **No `any` type** — Use `unknown` with type guards if type is uncertain
- **No `I` prefix on interfaces** — Use `UserProfile`, not `IUserProfile`
- **Use `as const` instead of enums** — Better tree-shaking and type inference
- **Barrel exports only at package boundaries** — Direct imports internally

{{/IF_HAS_TYPESCRIPT}}
{{#IF_HAS_NEXTJS}}
## Next.js Rules

- **Server Components by default** — Minimize `"use client"` boundaries
- **No direct API calls from client components** — Use Server Components or Server Actions
- **No business logic in page components** — Extract to separate functions/hooks
- **Image optimization** — Always use `next/image` for images

{{/IF_HAS_NEXTJS}}
{{#IF_HAS_NESTJS}}
## NestJS Rules

- **Controllers handle HTTP only** — Business logic lives in Services
- **Always validate DTOs** — Use class-validator decorators on every DTO
- **Use DI for everything** — Never instantiate dependencies directly
- **Guard separation** — Auth (JWT verification) and Roles (authorization) are separate guards

{{/IF_HAS_NESTJS}}
{{#IF_HAS_FASTAPI}}
## FastAPI Rules

- **Routes are thin** — Business logic lives in service modules
- **Use Pydantic models for all I/O** — Request bodies, responses, configs
- **Dependency injection for DB sessions** — Never create sessions directly in routes
- **Async by default** — Use `async def` for all route handlers

{{/IF_HAS_FASTAPI}}
{{#IF_HAS_DJANGO}}
## Django Rules

- **Fat models, thin views** — Business logic in models/managers, not views
- **Use Django ORM** — No raw SQL unless absolutely necessary
- **Migrations are immutable** — Never edit existing migration files
- **Use class-based views** — Unless the view is trivially simple

{{/IF_HAS_DJANGO}}
{{#IF_HAS_PRISMA}}
## Prisma Rules

- **Migrations via Prisma Migrate only** — No manual SQL schema changes
- **Always commit migration files** — `prisma/migrations/` is version-controlled
- **Use transactions for multi-table operations** — `prisma.$transaction()`

{{/IF_HAS_PRISMA}}
{{#IF_HAS_ALEMBIC}}
## Alembic Rules

- **Migrations via Alembic only** — No manual SQL schema changes
- **Always commit migration files** — `alembic/versions/` is version-controlled
- **Review auto-generated migrations** — `alembic revision --autogenerate` needs manual verification
- **Test migrations both up and down** — Ensure rollback works

{{/IF_HAS_ALEMBIC}}
{{#IF_HAS_DOCKER}}
## Docker Rules

- **Use docker-compose for local dev** — Don't run services directly on host
- **Never modify production Dockerfile without review** — Changes affect deployment
- **Use multi-stage builds** — Keep production images small

{{/IF_HAS_DOCKER}}
{{#IF_HAS_MONOREPO}}
## Monorepo Rules

- **Use workspace protocol** — `workspace:*` for inter-package dependencies
- **Shared types in packages/types** — Cross-package type definitions
- **Don't bypass turbo cache** — If you change `turbo.json` pipeline, get team review

{{/IF_HAS_MONOREPO}}
